"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-explainer-olympics-what-you-need-to-know-about-the-paris-2024-opening-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  PublishedJul 25, 2024, 07:45 PM  UpdatedJul 25, 2024, 07:45 PM  PARIS - Paris will officially kick off its Olympics extravaganza with an unprecedented opening ceremony on the river Seine on Friday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.372675410891463e-20, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1655340204020848e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is what you need to know about the ceremony:  WHEN AND WHERE IS THE OPENING CEREMONY TAKING PLACE?\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time, the Games' opening ceremony will not take place in a stadium.\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, around 85 boats will carry nearly 7,000 athletes on a 6km floating parade on the Seine, at the heart of Paris.\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.892076523280881e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 739, \"end\": 744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1655340204020848e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Departing from the Austerlitz bridge, they will sail past the Notre-Dame cathedral and arrive near the Eiffel Tower, after passing under bridges and gateways, including the Pont des Arts and Pont Neuf, and near many of the French capital's landmarks.\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 766, \"end\": 776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.9999397399027631, \"rank\": 6.026372853432809e-05, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\"}, {\"begin\": 920, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont des Arts\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\"}, {\"begin\": 938, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7790832693882765e-48, \"text\": \"Pont Neuf\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\"}, {\"begin\": 970, \"end\": 976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9550013066410926, \"rank\": 0.03860897887403337, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony is due to start at 7.30 p.m. (1730 GMT) and last about three hours and 45 minutes.\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1047, \"end\": 1050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.990427013124576e-22, \"text\": \"GMT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WHAT WILL WE SEE?\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have promised a show like no other.\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They say it will be daring and joyful and take advantage of the historic monuments, riverbanks, sky and water \\\"and there will not be a single riverbank or bridge that will not be filled with music, dance, or performance.\\\"\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 80 giant screens along the way will broadcast the show, which will include a floating parade of athletes and artists and is also expected to feature dancers performing from the roof of buildings along the Seine.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1596, \"end\": 1601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.892076523280881e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The show will be \\\"a large fresco\\\" celebrating Paris, France and the Games and will interweave the parade of athletes, artistic performances and elements of protocol, said Thomas Jolly, the artistic director of the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1650, \"end\": 1655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1655340204020848e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1657, \"end\": 1663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999996392971948, \"rank\": 3.117488714422787e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.762646344742971, \"rank\": 0.2755887745866513, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Details including who will light the Olympic cauldron to mark the start of the Games, or which artists are taking part, have been kept secret.\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Lady Gaga and Celine Dion are among singers who have been spotted in Paris, triggering rumours they could take part in the ceremony.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1985, \"end\": 1994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 1999, \"end\": 2010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.218713206848106e-45, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1655340204020848e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French media said Franco-Malian pop star Aya Nakamura, the most listened to French female singer in the world, will sing a song by the late Charles Aznavour.\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9550013066410926, \"rank\": 0.03860897887403337, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2160, \"end\": 2172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}, {\"begin\": 2195, \"end\": 2201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9550013066410926, \"rank\": 0.03860897887403337, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2259, \"end\": 2275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Aznavour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charles Aznavour\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Aznavour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Aznavour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nakamura was the target of racist abuse online when it was first rumoured that she would take part in the ceremony.\", \"from\": 2278, \"to\": 2393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She sings in French, with frequent use of slang, her style influenced by West Indies zouk music, mixing in American R'n'B and Afrobeats.\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2407, \"end\": 2413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9550013066410926, \"rank\": 0.03860897887403337, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2467, \"end\": 2478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\", \"score\": 0.9955442403427567, \"rank\": 0.004475600530920621, \"text\": \"West Indies\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\"}, {\"begin\": 2501, \"end\": 2509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999998921794, \"rank\": 1.0726380772784675e-09, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One big unknown is the weather.\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is currently forecast to be cloudy, when organisers were hoping there would be a \\\"golden hour\\\" of sunset lighting up buildings midway through the ceremony.\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WHO WILL BE THERE?\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2742, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The show will be attended by over 80 heads of state and government and more than 300,000 spectators will watch from the river's banks, organisers said.\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 committee said some 222,000 people would get free invites, while 104,000 will have to buy a ticket.\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 3011, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2901, \"end\": 2911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.007476956413212e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boats carrying the athletes will be equipped with cameras to allow those watching on TV or their phone to get a close-up view, the committee said.\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WHAT ABOUT SECURITY?\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organising the ceremony in the heart of an iconic city like Paris may make for great pictures, but it's also a major security challenge.\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3243, \"end\": 3248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1655340204020848e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 2,000 private security staff and 45,000 police will be dispatched to ensure the ceremony's security, including special intervention forces.\", \"from\": 3321, \"to\": 3465, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Snipers will be deployed on the top of buildings along the route.\", \"from\": 3466, \"to\": 3531, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An anti-drone system will be in place.\", \"from\": 3532, \"to\": 3570, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators and local residents need to carry permits on a QR code to get anywhere near the riverbanks.\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cars will not be allowed into the area, with few exceptions.\", \"from\": 3675, \"to\": 3735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nearby metro stations will be closed, as will many of the bridges.\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No planes will be allowed to fly over Paris - unless they are part of the ceremony.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3842, \"end\": 3847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1655340204020848e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With wars in Gaza and Ukraine, and security concerns at home, France already has its security alert at its highest level.\", \"from\": 3889, \"to\": 4010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3902, \"end\": 3906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.8172537400458776, \"rank\": 0.2236101849391889, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 3911, \"end\": 3918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.99999873308014, \"rank\": 1.2284702983786904e-06, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 3951, \"end\": 3957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999996392971948, \"rank\": 3.117488714422787e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials have said there are no specific terror threats to the ceremony.\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4085, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The main potential risk would be from a lone attacker, officials have said over the past months, while also flagging potential petty crime and possible protests, from environmental activists, the far right and far left, the pro-Palestinian movement or others.\", \"from\": 4087, \"to\": 4346, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A man was arrested in May in Saint-Etienne, suspected of planning an attack in the name of Islamic State at the city's soccer stadium during the Olympics.\", \"from\": 4348, \"to\": 4502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4377, \"end\": 4390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metz_Cathedral\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.24868306331354e-23, \"text\": \"Saint-Etienne\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q1370598\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metz_Cathedral\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metz_Cathedral\"}, {\"begin\": 4439, \"end\": 4452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.2135023383895097e-12, \"text\": \"Islamic State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A right-wing sympathiser was arrested in eastern France in July on suspicion of plotting attacks to take place during the Olympics.\", \"from\": 4504, \"to\": 4635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4553, \"end\": 4559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999996392971948, \"rank\": 3.117488714422787e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PAST SUMMER OLYMPICS' OPENING CEREMONIES  Tokyo 2020: The opening ceremony was overshadowed by the COVID-19 pandemic.\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4679, \"end\": 4684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999918145, \"rank\": 7.461792855381823e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4736, \"end\": 4753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9999987242835183, \"rank\": 1.1824092156505448e-06, \"text\": \"COVID-19 pandemic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Postponed by a year due to the coronavirus, the Games were held largely without spectators.\", \"from\": 4755, \"to\": 4846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rio 2016: Financially constrained Brazil had little choice but to put on a more low-key show, with minimal technology and a heavy dependence on the country's Carnival party traditions.\", \"from\": 4848, \"to\": 5032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4882, \"end\": 4888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9999999977312655, \"rank\": 2.165133534812025e-09, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 5006, \"end\": 5014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carnival\", \"score\": 0.9999543522645306, \"rank\": 4.489354889633286e-05, \"text\": \"Carnival\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carnival\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carnival\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"London 2012: The 86-year-old Queen Elizabeth put aside royal reserve in a video where she stepped onto a helicopter with James Bond actor Daniel Craig to be carried aloft from Buckingham Palace as part of a dizzying ceremony designed to highlight the grandeur and eccentricities of the nation.\", \"from\": 5034, \"to\": 5327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5063, \"end\": 5078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9999993930916412, \"rank\": 6.043833432126722e-07, \"text\": \"Queen Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 5095, \"end\": 5102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Military_reserve\", \"score\": 0.9991324673081261, \"rank\": 0.0006227056108939278, \"text\": \"reserve\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Military_reserve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Military_reserve\"}, {\"begin\": 5155, \"end\": 5165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond\", \"score\": 0.9967330968415204, \"rank\": 0.0032776107860573865, \"text\": \"James Bond\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond\"}, {\"begin\": 5172, \"end\": 5184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Craig\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daniel Craig\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Craig\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Craig\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beijing 2008: About one billion people, or 15% of the world's population, watched the opening ceremony, which involved 10,000 performers, 2008 drummers and a dramatic sky-walking finale.\", \"from\": 5329, \"to\": 5515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5329, \"end\": 5341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999272404, \"rank\": 7.288749642267166e-11, \"text\": \"Beijing 2008\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS  Olympics  France  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 5516, \"to\": 5658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5516, \"end\": 5523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 5535, \"end\": 5541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999996392971948, \"rank\": 3.117488714422787e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5575, \"end\": 5583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 5659, \"to\": 5673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 5675, \"to\": 5692, \"entities\": []}]}"